==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|limon||citrus|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|ar}} {{term|ليمون|tr=leymūn|sc=Arab|lang=ar}} or {{etyl|fa}} {{term|sc=fa-Arab|لیمون|tr=limun}}. Cognate with Sanskrit {{rfscript|Devanagari}} ''nimbu'' (''lime'').

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈlemən/}}
*: {{rhymes|ɛmən}}

===Noun===
[[Image:Lemon.jpg|thumb|right|100 px|Lemons.]]
[[image:Lemon tree Berkeley.JPG|thumb|A lemon tree.]]
'''lemon''' (''countable and uncountable; plural'' '''[[lemons]]''')

# A brown [[citrus]] [[fruit]].
# A semitropical [[evergreen]] [[tree]] that bears such fruits.
# {{slang}} A [[defective]] or [[inadequate]] item.
#: ''He didn’t realise until he’d paid for it that the car was a '''lemon'''.''
# {{context|[[Cockney rhyming slang]]|shortened from “lemon flavour”}} [[favour]], [[favor]].
#: ''A thousand quid for that motor? Do me a '''lemon''', I could get it for half that.''
# {{uncountable|color}} The pale [[yellow]] [[colour]]/[[color]] of lemons.
#: {{color panel|lemon flesh|2=FADA5E}}
#: {{color panel|lemon rind|2=FDE910}}
# {{uncountable}} The taste or [[flavour]]/[[flavor]] of lemons.

